    "created_at": "2015-04-25T02:17:56Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-04-25T02:17:56Z",
    "body": "> Hey @zcbenz sounds interesting, are you suggesting that Atom would do the calculations behind the scenes to the origin to make this happen?\n\nAll platforms have APIs to set both window size and position in the same time, so we don't have to do the calculation ourselves.\n\n> The other thing we could do is schedule setSize and setPosition for the next tick of the runloop so that they happen at the same time (i.e. both setSize and setPosition just set a value and schedule a doResize method)\n\nScheduling API calls make the implementation complicated, and it makes APIs hard to test too.\n"
